            1996]</commencementNote><sourceNote>(Format changes—<ref href="hk/2019/er1">E.R. 1 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote><section id="ID_1438403157656_003" name="s1" reason="omittedAsSpent" startPeriod="2019-04-11" status="omitted" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><sourceNote>(Omitted as spent—<ref href="hk/2019/er1">E.R. 1 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote></section><section id="ID_1438403157671_002" name="s2" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-04-11" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Interpretation</heading><leadIn>In this Regulation—</leadIn><def name="Formwork"><term>formwork</term>
                (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">模板</term>) means any type of metallic, wooden or
            fibreglass construction including any structural support designed to enable concrete,
            cement or other material poured in a fluid state to assume a particular shape upon
            setting;</def><def name="Hammering"><term>hammering</term>
                (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">敲擊</term>) means to strike repeatedly any object,
            instrument or surface with any other object, instrument or surface;</def><def name="Rubble"><term>rubble</term>
                (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">瓦礫</term>) means any kind of debris or superfluous
            material arising from construction work including bricks, concrete, metal, glass, wood,
            plastic, earth, rock, bamboo or fibreglass;</def><def name="Scaffolding"><term>scaffolding</term>
                (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">棚架</term>) means any type of construction made of
            metal, wood or bamboo whose purpose is to enable temporary access to a part or parts of
            another structure or building whether completed or not.</def></section><section id="ID_1438403157687_001" name="s3" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-04-11" status="operational" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Construction work</heading><content>The construction work in the <ref>Schedule</ref> is prescribed for the purpose of <ref>section 6(2)</ref> of the Ordinance.</content></section><schedule id="ID_1438403157687_003" name="sch0" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-04-11" status="operational" temporalId="sch0"><num value="0">Schedule</num><note class="align_right" role="crossReferences" type="inline">[<ref href="/hk/cap400G/s3">s.
                3</ref>]<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></note><subsection id="ID_1438412395770_026" name="1" temporalId="sch0_1"><num value="1" class="align_left">1.</num><content>Erection or dismantling of formwork or
                scaffolding</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1438412395770_034" name="2" temporalId="sch0_2" class="no_header"><num value="2" class="align_left">2.</num><content>Loading, unloading or handling of rubble, wooden boards, steel bars, wood or
                scaffolding
                material</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1438412395770_042" name="3" temporalId="sch0_3"><num value="3" class="align_left">3.</num><content>Hammering</content></subsection><sourceNote>(<ref href="hk/2019/er1">E.R. 1 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote></schedule></main></subLeg>